			<div class="comment_body">
				<div class="comment_time">
					2 hours ago ( 6:13 PM)				</div>

																												
				People should calm down a bit.<br />
Following are historical facts supported by disclosed, first hand documents.  <br />
<br />
Q: Business facts?<br />
<br />
A: Brothels were privately owned and operated by Koreans, Chinese and Japanese, serviced mostly by Korean, Chinese and Japanese prostitutes.<br />
Strictly regulated by Japanese law.<br />
Health checks and payments to prostitutes were recorded.<br />
If debt free, women were free to leave, although many remained for the good pay.<br />
<br />
Q: Why claims of abduction and forced slavery?<br />
<br />
A: Not uncommon for poor families to "sell" their daughters to "buyers" (Korean/Chinese/Japanese) that sell girls to brothels. Girl needs to pay off debt by working as prostitute.  <br />
[Assumption: Given customers were mostly Japanese soldiers, natural for her to think she was put into tragic circumstance by JP military.] While large proportion of women entered profession willingly, cases as above existed. Also, isolated cases of crimes committed by corrupt military officers have been reported.  <br />
<br />
Q: So were these brothels closed down by Americans?<br />
<br />
A: See this photo "American soldiers lining up to receive comfort services in postwar Japan" > <a href="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0e/Yasuura_House.jpg" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0e/Yasuura_House.jpg</a><br />
Officially supported by US and financed by Japan, "comfort houses" were established across nation to provide sexual services to American soldiers. Account of 10,000 Japanese women raped by US troops during war prompted authorities to provide professionally regulated service to insure public's safety. Operated by "Recreation and Amusement Association", hundreds of women applied daily, with total of 53,000 employed.			</div>
			
